{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775859167141,"sessionID":"ses_2868bbf9bffewN9nmTmbsFM6Qm","part":{"id":"prt_d79746b49001aUVY5hjKHjO04Q","messageID":"msg_d797462e4001PE2dx459fPw8FW","sessionID":"ses_2868bbf9bffewN9nmTmbsFM6Qm","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_43dddcdcce224613a2115c07","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md","limit":200},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-019 — CLI Binary Entry Points (4 Binaries)\n2: \n3: - **AR ID**: AR-019\n4: - **Module**: cmd\n5: - **Language**: Go\n6: - **Size**: M\n7: - **Status**: ST-1 Completed (design.md)\n8: \n9: ## 1. Architecture\n10: \n11: ### 1.1 Overview\n12: \n13: AgentCube provides four CLI binary entry points for its Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform. Each binary serves a distinct role in the system architecture, communicating via the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group using the generated client-go library.\n14: \n15: ### 1.2 Binary Overview\n16: \n17: | Binary | Purpose | Port | Dependencies |\n18: |--------|---------|------|--------------|\n19: | `agentd` | K8s Reconciler Controller | N/A | K8s API Server, etcd |\n20: | `picod` | Code Execution Daemon | 8080 (configurable) | Local filesystem |\n21: | `router` | HTTP Session Router | 8080 | Redis/Valkey, WorkloadManager |\n22: | `workload-manager` | Sandbox Lifecycle Manager | 8080 | K8s API Server, Redis/Valkey |\n23: \n24: ### 1.3 Component Structure\n25: \n26: ```\n27: cmd/\n28: ├── agentd/\n29: │   ├── main.go                      # Controller entry point\n30: │   └── ...\n31: ├── picod/\n32: │   ├── main.go                      # Code execution daemon entry\n33: │   └── ...\n34: ├── router/\n35: │   ├── main.go                      # Router entry point\n36: │   └── ...\n37: └── workload-manager/\n38:     ├── main.go                      # Workload manager entry point\n39:     └── ...\n40: ```\n41: \n42: ### 1.4 Architecture Diagram\n43: \n44: ```\n45: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n46: │                              AgentCube System                                │\n47: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n48: │                                                                             │\n49: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n50: │  │                        agentd (Controller)                           │   │\n51: │  │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │   │\n52: │  │  │  Watches: AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter CRDs                 │  │   │\n53: │  │  │  Creates: Pods, Services, ConfigMaps                          │  │   │\n54: │  │  │  Status Updates: AgentRuntimeStatus, CodeInterpreterStatus    │  │   │\n55: │  │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │   │\n56: │  └──────────────────────────────┬────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n57: │                                 │                                             │\n58: │                                 │ K8s API                                     │\n59: │                                 ▼                                             │\n60: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n61: │  │                    Kubernetes API Server                             │   │\n62: │  │  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌────────────────────┐   │   │\n63: │  │  │ AgentRuntime    │  │ CodeInterpreter │  │ Pod/Service/Config │   │   │\n64: │  │  │ (CRD)          │  │ (CRD)           │  │ (Native resources)│   │   │\n65: │  │  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────────┘  └────────────────────┘   │   │\n66: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n67: │                                    │                                         │\n68: ├────────────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────┤\n69: │                                    │                                         │\n70: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────┴─────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n71: │  │                    workload-manager                                 │   │\n72: │  │  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────┐   │   │\n73: │  │  │ HTTP API    │  │ Sandbox CRUD │  │ Session Lifecycle       │   │   │\n74: │  │  │ (Gin)       │  │              │  │                         │   │   │\n75: │  │  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────────────────┘   │   │\n76: │  └──────────────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n77: │                                 │                                           │\n78: │                                 │ Session events                            │\n79: │                                 ▼                                           │\n80: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n81: │  │                    Redis/Valkey (Session Store)                     │   │\n82: │  │  - Session data (session-routing)                                   │   │\n83: │  │  - Sandbox state                                                    │   │\n84: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n85: │                                    │                                         │\n86: │                                    │ Proxy routing                           │\n87: │                                    ▼                                         │\n88: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n89: │  │                         router                                      │   │\n90: │  │  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────┐   │   │\n91: │  │  │ Session     │  │ Auth/JWT    │  │ Backend Health Check    │   │   │\n92: │  │  │ Routing     │  │ Middleware  │  │                          │   │   │\n93: │  │  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────────────────┘   │   │\n94: │  └──────────────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n95: │                                 │                                           │\n96: │                                 │ HTTP Requests                             │\n97: │                                 ▼                                           │\n98: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n99: │  │                      Sandbox Pods                                   │   │\n100: │  │  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────┐   │   │\n101: │  │  │ Agent        │  │ Code         │  │ Services                 │   │   │\n102: │  │  │ Container    │  │ Interpreter  │  │ (NodePort/ClusterIP)    │   │   │\n103: │  │  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────────────────┘   │   │\n104: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n105: │                                    │                                         │\n106: │                                    │ Optional                                │\n107: │                                    ▼                                         │\n108: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n109: │  │                         picod                                       │   │\n110: │  │  - Code execution daemon inside sandbox pods                       │   │\n111: │  │  - File operations, execution                                       │   │\n112: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n113: │                                                                             │\n114: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n115: ```\n116: \n117: ### 1.5 Data Flow\n118: \n119: ```\n120:                                     ┌─────────────────┐\n121:                                     │   Client Request│\n122:                                     └────────┬────────┘\n123:                                              │\n124:                                              ▼\n125:                                ┌─────────────────────────┐\n126:                                │      router             │\n127:                                │  ┌───────────────────┐  │\n128:                                │  │ Auth Middleware   │  │\n129:                                │  │ JWT/Token Review  │  │\n130:                                │  └───────────────────┘  │\n131:                                │            │            │\n132:                                │            ▼            │\n133:                                │  ┌───────────────────┐  │\n134:                                │  │ Session Manager   │  │\n135:                                │  │ → Redis lookup    │  │\n136:                                │  └───────────────────┘  │\n137:                                │            │            │\n138:                                │            ▼            │\n139:                                │  ┌───────────────────┐  │\n140:                                │  │ Backend Selector  │  │\n141:                                │  │ → WorkloadManager │  │\n142:                                │  └───────────────────┘  │\n143:                                └───────────┬─────────────┘\n144:                                            │\n145:                                            ▼\n146:                                ┌─────────────────────────┐\n147:                                │  workload-manager      │\n148:                                │  ┌───────────────────┐  │\n149:                                │  │ API Handlers      │  │\n150:                                │  │ GET/POST/DELETE   │  │\n151:                                │  └───────────────────┘  │\n152:                                │            │            │\n153:                                │            ▼            │\n154:                                │  ┌───────────────────┐  │\n155:                                │  │ Client-go         │  │\n156:                                │  │ → K8s API         │  │\n157:                                │  └───────────────────┘  │\n158:                                └───────────┬─────────────┘\n159:                                            │\n160:                                            ▼\n161:                                ┌─────────────────────────┐\n162:                                │  Kubernetes API Server  │\n163:                                │  - Create AgentRuntime │\n164:                                │  - Create Pod/Service  │\n165:                                └───────────┬─────────────┘\n166:                                            │\n167:                                            ▼\n168:                                ┌─────────────────────────┐\n169:                                │      agentd             │\n170:                                │  ┌───────────────────┐  │\n171:                                │  │ Controller        │  │\n172:                                │  │ → Reconcile loop  │  │\n173:                                │  └───────────────────┘  │\n174:                                └─────────────────────────┘\n175: ```\n176: \n177: ## 2. Binary Specifications\n178: \n179: ### 2.1 agentd — Kubernetes Controller\n180: \n181: **Entry Point**: `cmd/agentd/main.go`\n182: \n183: The agentd binary runs as a Kubernetes controller using controller-runtime. It watches `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` custom resources and ensures the desired runtime state matches the actual cluster state.\n184: \n185: #### Command-Line Flags\n186: \n187: | Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n188: |------|------|---------|-------------|\n189: | `--metrics-bind-address` | string | \"0\" | Metrics server bind address (0 = disabled) |\n190: | `--health-probe-bind-address` | string | \"0\" | Health probe bind address |\n191: | `--leader-elect` | bool | false | Enable leader election |\n192: | `--leader-elect-lease-duration` | duration | 15s | Leader election lease duration |\n193: | `--leader-elect-renew-deadline` | duration | 10s | Leader election renew deadline |\n194: | `--leader-elect-retry-period` | duration | 5s | Leader election retry period |\n195: \n196: #### Configuration\n197: \n198: ```go\n199: type AgentdConfig struct {\n200:     // Metrics server configuration\n\n(Showing lines 1-200 of 740. Use offset=201 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-019 — CLI Binary Entry Points (4 Binaries)\n\n- **AR ID**: AR-019\n- **Module**: cmd\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: M\n- **Status**: ST-1 Completed (design.md)\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Overview\n\nAgentCube provides four CLI binary entry points for its Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform. Each binary serves a distinct role in the system architecture, communicating via the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group using the generated client-go library.\n\n### 1.2 Binary Overview\n\n| Binary | Purpose | Port | Dependencies |\n|--------|---------|------|--------------|\n| `agentd` | K8s Reconciler Controller | N/A | K8s API Server, etcd |\n| `picod` | Code Execution Daemon | 8080 (configurable) | Local filesystem |","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775859167114,"end":1775859167138}}}}
