{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775859178509,"sessionID":"ses_2868bbf9bffewN9nmTmbsFM6Qm","part":{"id":"prt_d797496bc001mChZGNoy465rQT","messageID":"msg_d79748b62001osowtUBOHtvpKG","sessionID":"ses_2868bbf9bffewN9nmTmbsFM6Qm","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_d4537da620ab4a639f871e2f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md","limit":200,"offset":200},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n200:     // Metrics server configuration\n201:     MetricsBindAddress string\n202:     \n203:     // Health probe configuration  \n204:     HealthProbeBindAddress string\n205:     \n206:     // Leader election\n207:     LeaderElect        bool\n208:     LeaseDuration      time.Duration\n209:     RenewDeadline      time.Duration\n210:     RetryPeriod        time.Duration\n211:     \n212:     // Namespace to watch (empty = all namespaces)\n213:     WatchNamespace     string\n214:     \n215:     // Sync period for full reconciliation\n216:     SyncPeriod         time.Duration\n217:     \n218:     // Max concurrent reconciles\n219:     MaxConcurrentReconciles int\n220: }\n221: ```\n222: \n223: #### Dependencies\n224: \n225: - `pkg/agentd/` — Controller implementation\n226: - `pkg/client/informers/` — Generated informers\n227: - `pkg/client/listers/` — Generated listers\n228: - `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/` — API types\n229: \n230: ### 2.2 picod — Code Execution Daemon\n231: \n232: **Entry Point**: `cmd/picod/main.go`\n233: \n234: The picod binary runs inside sandbox pods as a code execution daemon, providing file operations and code execution capabilities.\n235: \n236: #### Command-Line Flags\n237: \n238: | Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n239: |------|------|---------|-------------|\n240: | `--port` | int | 8080 | Server listen port |\n241: | `--workspace` | string | \"\" | Root directory for file operations (default: cwd) |\n242: | `--auth-mode` | string | \"picod\" | Authentication mode: picod, none |\n243: | `--session-timeout` | duration | 15m | Session timeout |\n244: | `--max-session-duration` | duration | 8h | Maximum session duration |\n245: \n246: #### Configuration\n247: \n248: ```go\n249: type PicoDConfig struct {\n250:     Port              int\n251:     Workspace         string\n252:     AuthMode          string\n253:     SessionTimeout    time.Duration\n254:     MaxSessionDuration time.Duration\n255: }\n256: ```\n257: \n258: #### API Endpoints\n259: \n260: | Method | Path | Description |\n261: |--------|------|-------------|\n262: | GET | `/health` | Health check |\n263: | POST | `/execute` | Execute code |\n264: | GET | `/files/*path` | Read file |\n265: | PUT | `/files/*path` | Write file |\n266: | DELETE | `/files/*path` | Delete file |\n267: \n268: #### Dependencies\n269: \n270: - `pkg/picod/` — Server implementation\n271: \n272: ### 2.3 router — HTTP Session Router\n273: \n274: **Entry Point**: `cmd/router/main.go`\n275: \n276: The router binary provides HTTP routing with session management, authentication, and proxy capabilities. It routes incoming requests to the appropriate sandbox backend based on session affinity.\n277: \n278: #### Command-Line Flags\n279: \n280: | Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n281: |------|------|---------|-------------|\n282: | `--listen-address` | string | \":8080\" | Server listen address |\n283: | `--workload-manager-url` | string | \"\" | WorkloadManager backend URL (required) |\n284: | `--backend-timeout` | duration | 30s | Backend request timeout |\n285: | `--idle-timeout` | duration | 60s | Idle connection timeout |\n286: | `--health-check-interval` | duration | 10s | Health check interval |\n287: | `--health-check-timeout` | duration | 5s | Health check timeout |\n288: | `--max-conns-per-backend` | int | 100 | Max connections per backend |\n289: | `--rate-limit-enabled` | bool | false | Enable rate limiting |\n290: | `--rate-limit-rps` | int | 10 | Rate limit RPS |\n291: | `--auth-enabled` | bool | false | Enable authentication |\n292: | `--auth-token` | string | \"\" | Bearer token for auth |\n293: | `--session-enabled` | bool | false | Enable session management |\n294: | `--session-timeout` | duration | 30m | Session timeout |\n295: | `--session-cookie-name` | string | \"AGENTSESSIONID\" | Session cookie name |\n296: | `--jwt-enabled` | bool | false | Enable JWT authentication |\n297: | `--jwt-secret` | string | \"\" | JWT secret for HS256 |\n298: | `--jwt-private-key-path` | string | \"\" | Path to RS256 private key |\n299: | `--jwt-public-key-path` | string | \"\" | Path to RS256 public key |\n300: \n301: #### Configuration\n302: \n303: ```go\n304: type RouterConfig struct {\n305:     ListenAddress       string\n306:     WorkloadManagerURL string\n307:     \n308:     // Backend\n309:     BackendTimeout      time.Duration\n310:     IdleTimeout         time.Duration\n311:     HealthCheckInterval time.Duration\n312:     HealthCheckTimeout  time.Duration\n313:     MaxConnsPerBackend  int\n314:     \n315:     // Rate limiting\n316:     RateLimitEnabled    bool\n317:     RateLimitRPS        int\n318:     \n319:     // Auth\n320:     AuthEnabled         bool\n321:     AuthToken           string\n322:     \n323:     // Session management\n324:     SessionEnabled         bool\n325:     SessionTimeout         time.Duration\n326:     SessionCookieName      string\n327:     SessionMaxActive       int\n328:     SessionCookieSecure    bool\n329:     SessionCookieHTTPOnly  bool\n330:     SessionCookieDomain    string\n331:     SessionCleanupInterval time.Duration\n332:     \n333:     // JWT\n334:     JWTEnabled           bool\n335:     JWTAlgorithm         string\n336:     JWTSecret            string\n337:     JWTPrivateKeyPath    string\n338:     JWTPublicKeyPath     string\n339:     JWTIssuer            string\n340:     JWTAudience          []string\n341:     JWTExpiration        time.Duration\n342:     JWTRefreshExpiration time.Duration\n343:     JWTClockSkew         time.Duration\n344:     JWTAllowQueryParam   bool\n345: }\n346: ```\n347: \n348: #### Dependencies\n349: \n350: - `pkg/router/` — Router implementation\n351: - `pkg/store/` — Session store (Redis/Valkey)\n352: - `pkg/client/clientset/` — Generated client-go\n353: \n354: ### 2.4 workload-manager — Sandbox Lifecycle Manager\n355: \n356: **Entry Point**: `cmd/workload-manager/main.go`\n357: \n358: The workload-manager binary provides REST APIs for sandbox lifecycle management. It creates and manages AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources in Kubernetes.\n359: \n360: #### Command-Line Flags\n361: \n362: | Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n363: |------|------|---------|-------------|\n364: | `--listen-address` | string | \":8080\" | Server listen address |\n365: | `--store-type` | string | \"redis\" | Store type: redis, valkey |\n366: | `--store-address` | string | \"localhost:6379\" | Store address |\n367: | `--store-password` | string | \"\" | Store password |\n368: | `--store-db` | int | 0 | Store database number |\n369: | `--namespace` | string | \"default\" | Default Kubernetes namespace |\n370: | `--session-timeout` | duration | 15m | Default session timeout |\n371: | `--max-session-duration` | duration | 8h | Default max session duration |\n372: | `--gc-interval` | duration | 5m | Garbage collection interval |\n373: | `--gc-worker-count` | int | 5 | GC worker count |\n374: \n375: #### Configuration\n376: \n377: ```go\n378: type WorkloadManagerConfig struct {\n379:     // Server\n380:     ListenAddress string\n381:     \n382:     // Store (Redis/Valkey)\n383:     StoreType    string\n384:     StoreAddress string\n385:     StorePassword string\n386:     StoreDB      int\n387:     \n388:     // Kubernetes\n389:     Namespace string\n390:     \n391:     // Session defaults\n392:     SessionTimeout       time.Duration\n393:     MaxSessionDuration   time.Duration\n394:     \n395:     // Garbage collection\n396:     GCInterval     time.Duration\n397:     GCWorkerCount  int\n398:     \n399:     // Webhook configuration (optional)\n\n(Showing lines 200-399 of 740. Use offset=400 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"    // Metrics server configuration\n    MetricsBindAddress string\n    \n    // Health probe configuration  \n    HealthProbeBindAddress string\n    \n    // Leader election\n    LeaderElect        bool\n    LeaseDuration      time.Duration\n    RenewDeadline      time.Duration\n    RetryPeriod        time.Duration\n    \n    // Namespace to watch (empty = all namespaces)\n    WatchNamespace     string\n    \n    // Sync period for full reconciliation\n    SyncPeriod         time.Duration\n    \n    // Max concurrent reconciles\n    MaxConcurrentReconciles int","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775859178492,"end":1775859178507}}}}
